com.fuzzylimes.jsr.clients

Class GameClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fuzzylimes.jsr.clients.GameClient

  • public class GameClient
extends Object

    This client is used to make requests to the /games set of resources on SpeedRun.com's API. The official documentation for this set of APIs can be found in the API Docs.

    Games are the thing that runs are being done against. They are exactly what they are called - the video game that is being played.

    The client uses static methods for all of the resource calls, so there is now need to initialize anything to make a request. Simply reference the resource you wish to use to retrieve a related pojo.

      • getDerivedGames

        public static PagedResponse<Game> getDerivedGames(String id,
                                                  GamesQuery queryParams,
                                                  Sorting<GamesOrderBy> order,
                                                  Boolean embed)
                                           throws IOException,
                                                  UnexpectedResponseException

        GET games/{id}/derived-games

        Used to retrieve all of the games that have the given game id set as their base game. This is used specifically to relate romhacks or fan games back to their original game. Will return a PagedResponse of Game objects, filtered by a set of provided GamesQuery query params, sorted by the parameters defined in Sorting of type GamesOrderBy, and optionally enriched with embedded data objects.

        • Supports query parameters available in GamesQuery
        • Supports Order by and Direction in GamesOrderBy and Direction
        • Supports embedding with
        • API Docs
        Parameters:
        id - the id or abbreviation of the game being queried
        queryParams - Additional query params to filter the output, provided by GamesQuery
        order - Defined sorting order; Sorting of type GamesOrderBy
        embed - whether or not to embed all additional, supported, embed items
        Returns:
        a PagedResponse of Game objects
        Throws:
        IOException - if something goes wrong with mapping
        UnexpectedResponseException - if non-2XX or no body returned to request
